{
  "doc_id": "46365",
  "text": "A recent approach, MCSEnumerator, circumvents this issue and allows enumeration of MCSs and cMCSs in GSMMs. Case studies using an E. coli GSMM resulted in compound overproduction strategies not greater than seven knockouts for various case studies, including serine, fumarate and ethanol production [CITATION_1] . The algorithm employs a mixed-integer linear programming (MILP) problem that combines two approaches from earlier work. The first is a mathematical formulation in which a dual-system is generated so that EMs calculated in it correspond to the primal system in which it was based [CITATION_2] . The second approach concerns the K-shortest algorithm for partial EM enumeration, allowing enumeration of the smallest EMs using a simple MILP formulation [CITATION_3] . By combining these two approaches, one can find the smallest EMs in the dual system and thus, the smallest MCSs for the original model.",
